 The test suite ended up being more extensive than the above suggests. Beyond the parser, height curve, BoundingBox, ShapeBuilder, and AdaptivePath tests, I also wrote PathfinderTest, EdgeTest, GraphBuilderTest, OsmElementTest, RelationTest, and UtilityToolsTest — over 1200 lines of tests in total, covering haversine distance calculations, adjacency list construction, edge weights, element tag handling, and coordinate transforms.

 I also replaced the boolean isDijkstra flag in the pathfinding API with a proper Algorithm enum with DIJKSTRA and A_STAR values. Using an enum makes the callsites readable and also worked cleanly as a JMH @Param for running parameterized benchmarks across both algorithms. On the rendering side I removed the Drawable interface that had been sitting as an empty abstraction — I deleted the interface and removed the draws(Graphics2D) implementations from Node, Way, Relation, and HeightCurve, so all drawing logic now lives exclusively in the dedicated renderer classes where it belongs.